        "description": "Predicted normalized hemolysis index (NIH) must fall within the expanded experimental uncertainty band (k=2) at all 5 flow-speed operating points. Pressure head prediction error must be below 5%."
      },
      "rationale": "NIH predictions at all 5 operating points fall within k=2 experimental uncertainty bands. Mean absolute error: 3.8% on NIH; 2.1% on pressure head. Worst-case operating point (3 L/min, 3500 RPM): predicted NIH 0.0041 mg/100L vs experimental 0.0039±0.0006 mg/100L. Validation metric E/D < 1 at all points."
