        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI directly maps to clinical hemolysis endpoint and regulatory acceptance criterion",
        "description": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be the same metric used in the regulatory submission and directly linked to the clinical endpoint of red blood cell damage. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 must be the decision criterion."
      },
      "rationale": "NIH is the FDA-accepted metric for CPB hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance on blood-contacting devices. RH < 1 criterion directly implements the predicate comparison required by 510(k) pathway. QoI traceability from clinical endpoint (plasma-free hemoglobin) to NIH documented in model development report MDR-2023-04."
