        "description": "Validation experiments must use the FDA GCBP geometry (or geometric surrogate with documented similarity), the same blood analog fluid, and operating conditions spanning the full COU operating envelope. No extrapolation beyond validated range permitted."
      },
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on FDA GCBP geometry using porcine blood at 37±0.5°C, hematocrit 38±2%, across 5 operating points spanning the full COU envelope (3–7 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Geometric similarity verified by CMM measurement of test article (deviation < 0.05 mm from nominal). No extrapolation required."
