        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Turbulence and hemolysis sub-model selection justified by literature and sensitivity; model form uncertainty quantified",
        "description": "Turbulence model selection (SST k-omega) and hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) must be justified by peer-reviewed literature for rotating hemodynamic devices. Model form uncertainty must be quantified by comparing at least two turbulence model variants; contribution to total uncertainty must be documented."
      },
      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected based on systematic review of 12 published CPB CFD studies; shown superior to k-epsilon and RSM for swirling confined flows at Re 10,000–80,000. Model form uncertainty quantified by comparing SST k-omega vs. transitional SST: NIH difference 4.2%, incorporated into total uncertainty budget. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model validated against Heuser-Opitz data; applicability within shear stress range 1–500 Pa confirmed."
    },
    {
